    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Powdery alkaline compound used in paper pulp manufacture and mass deacidification treatments. Magnesium hydroxide is found in nature as the mineral brucite. It is used medicinally as a laxative and antacid. As a suspension in water it is commonly known as milk of magnesia.</Note_Text>
